enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve creating a new PredicatedSortedMap instance with a subset of the original map, requiring similar initialization and predicate validation.
Both methods return a subset of the original map, with headMap focusing on the elements before a given key, and subMap focusing on a range of keys.
Both methods return a subset of the original map, with tailMap focusing on the elements after a given key, and subMap focusing on a range of keys.
The validate method can be used to assert that the keys and values in the resulting subMap meet the specified predicates, ensuring the integrity of the map subset.
The put method can be used to test the behavior of adding new entries to the subMap, ensuring that the predicates are still enforced.
The putAll method can be used to test the behavior of adding multiple entries to the subMap, ensuring that the predicates are still enforced.
